title: new chapter!
body:
https://archiveofourown.org/works/10982043/chapters/35660673

Tony landed and stepped out of the suit. “Well first off she’s really great, you just have to see past the whole PTSD/I’m-going-to-kill-everyone-that-touches-me vibe that she has. And also, she’s technically not able to be arrested by you because she’s out of your jurisdiction.”

Fury’s face was impassive. “Everyone is in my jurisdiction.”

“Actually, director, we agreed after the I was sent to Earth to be reformed, Thor and I would handle off-world beings since we know a lot more about them than you do.” Loki spoke up, his defensive position in front of Alice unchanging.

Fury sighed. “Yes, aliens are not technically in my jurisdiction but mutants are, and that’s what Alice is.”


woah woah woah…learning more about who Alice really is…watch out because after this Alice and Loki get a lot of alone time…

title: Getting it Right
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2LoWaAi

by Akira_of_the_Twilight

prompt: Tony fucks up a really small thing in their relationship (Forgets something or says something stupid.) and is really scared that bucky will break up with him. Bucky reassures his stupid anxious boyfriend.

Of all nights, why did tonight have to be the one in which a mandatory emergency meeting had been held at SI?

It wasn’t Tony first time showing up late to a date because of work, but after last night, saying it was in “poor taste” was putting it mildly (and in such a spectacularly stupid way too). This date was a miracle after the way he’d screwed up last night. He was practically throwing the date in Bucky’s face.

There was no way Bucky would forgive him after this.

title: A Working Condition
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2uRMBj7

by saavik13

When they were little, Thor tried his best to protect his brother. It did not always work, but Loki was grateful none the less. But they are a long lived race and distance builds between even the closest of bonds.

Darcy has always known what she was, but never thought she would find a place, or a people, that understood. Than one large blond god runs smack into the front of her truck. Perhaps things can be both complicated and good? She wouldn’t know but she’ll sure as hell give it a go.
